  <section>
    <h2>Single-Open Mode</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-single</code> to allow only one panel to be open at a time. When a panel opens, any other open panel will close automatically.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <accordion-wc data-single>
        <details name="single-demo" open>
          <summary>First Panel (open by default)</summary>
          <div>
            <p>This panel is open by default. Click another panel to see it close.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details name="single-demo">
          <summary>Second Panel</summary>
          <div>
            <p>Opening this panel will automatically close the first one.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details name="single-demo">
          <summary>Third Panel</summary>
          <div>
            <p>Only one panel can be open at a time in single mode.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </accordion-wc>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Single-open mode accordion">{{ singleModeCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <aside class="note">
      <strong>Note:</strong> For browsers that support the <code>name</code> attribute on <code>&lt;details&gt;</code>, exclusive behavior is handled natively. The component provides a JavaScript polyfill for older browsers.
    </aside>
  </section>

